{{wikipediapar|Dorothy Dix}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Named after US advice columnist [[w:Dorothy Dix|Dorothy Dix]] (1870-1951) and reputedly from Dix herself inventing some of the more interesting readers' questions she answered.
===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# {{AU}} A [[question]] asked of a [[minister]] by a member of his own [[party]], to give the minister the opportunity to [[promote]] the [[government]]'s work, [[criticize]] the [[opposition]], etc.
